<li aria-level="1">All one line to root’s crontab (via <code>sudo crontab -e</code>):
<ul>
<li aria-level="1"><code>@reboot if [[ `grep tid /etc/pam.d/sudo` ]]; then echo "TouchID already enabled"; else echo "# sudo: auth account password sessionn auth       sufficient     pam_smartcard.sonauth       sufficient     pam_tid.sonauth       required       pam_opendirectory.sonaccount    required       pam_permit.sonpassword   required       pam_deny.sonsession    required       pam_permit.so" &gt; /etc/pam.d/sudo; echo "Enabling TouchID for sudo"; fi</code></li>
</ul>
